parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Heat from Engine and Exhaust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat generated by the engine and exhaust can cause burns to the rider's legs, especially in hot weather or during prolonged idling, which can lead to serious injuries and affect the rider's safety.
symptoms: Intense heat coming from the engine
exhaust burns rider's legs
especially in hot weather or during prolonged idling
heat is so intense it can cause mild burns to legs during riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Throttle Management System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities. The failure of the throttle management system can also cause the engine to shut off without warning, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the throttle management system fails
the engine warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the vehicle suddenly shuts off without warning
the vehicle is unable to start
the vehicle experiences intermittent stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Module and Fuse Block Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical module and fuse block can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. This failure can also cause other electrical systems to malfunction, further compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the electrical module fails
the fuse block fails
the engine warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the vehicle experiences intermittent electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Brake Lockup in Reverse Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended brake lockup in reverse gear can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, especially when reversing out of a parking spot or driveway.
symptoms: The brakes seem to lock up when shifting into reverse gear
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when reversing
the brake pedal must be pressed to release the brakes
the park brake does not hold
excessive wear on brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inconsistent Brake Performance and Premature Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent brake performance and premature wear can lead to reduced stopping power, increased risk of accidents, and higher maintenance costs.
symptoms: Excessive wear on brake pads
inconsistent brake pedal feel
brakes may grab or lock up unexpectedly
poor fuel economy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the park brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The park brake does not hold
the vehicle rolls or moves when parked on an incline
the park brake is adjusted to its maximum setting but still does not hold.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wheel Separation Due to Lug Nut Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of a wheel due to lug nut failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries.
symptoms: The wheel detaches from the vehicle while in motion
the vehicle veers off the road
the driver and passenger may be ejected
the detached wheel can strike other vehicles or objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Lug nut failure can lead to wheel separation, loss of control, and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The lug nuts detach from the wheel hub
the wheel becomes loose or separates from the vehicle
the vehicle may vibrate or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of the rear tire can cause the rider to lose control of the motorcycle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration while riding
sudden loss of control
rear tire comes off while in motion
tire travels a distance before stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improperly Secured or Defective Wheel Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A wheel assembly that is not properly secured or is defective can cause the tire to separate while in motion, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration while riding
sudden loss of control
rear tire comes off while in motion
tire travels a distance before stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly inspect or ensure the quality of wheel assemblies can lead to defects or improper installation, resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration while riding
sudden loss of control
rear tire comes off while in motion
tire travels a distance before stopping.
